Best tacos in NYC and mexican restaurant!!!

Blue Corn is very good & consistent. We've been ordering here for several years, and everything's always been good with no major hiccups. For a long time It used to be called La Oaxaceña for most of those years, which was about the same as I can tell. I think they rebranded, the food hasn't changed much (a good thing). Food is fresh and tasty- go tos for me are tacos, enchilada platters (molé), rice & beans, tortas, fried thin meat milanesa / veg platter items...some reviewer below said the tacos are weaK- I disagree. Had them all. Make sure to get then fully loaded, con todo. For NYC it's top notch value compared to more hipster places dtown and brooklyn. Queens is comparable. Comes with the meat, lettuce, herbs, tomato, cheese, onion, with the double tortilla- these tacos are substantial. 4 tacos and a small rice and beans Is a solid meal and good value. I'm not a small guy. Meals come with a good spicy tomatillo sauce. Also pre covid I've eaten there inside several times. It's clean and chill. staff is nice. Takeout always packaged neatly. A good local neighborhood establishment to support, owned and operated by ppl who care a lot more than average.

if you want authentic mexican food dont come here. the toppings are literally iceberg lettuce and slices of tomato... ive never been to an authentic mexican restaurant that does not have pico de gallo, i mean dam even chipotle has it. they also dont even use cilantro and onion, a topping which is a staple. the prices are super outrageous for food that lacks flavor and authenticity. would not recommend.

We got two orders of the tacos dorados from here for take-out. They were great! the  staff was very nice as well. $10 for 5 rolled tacos topped with cheese, sour cream and all the trimming. Wonderful little experience!
